verbose_text: Of note, the percent inhibition of renal glucose reabsorption by dapagliflozin at a plasma glucose level of 5.6 mmol/L (100 mg/dL) was ~ 20% in healthy subjects and 27% in type 2 diabetic subjects (XREF_FIG) and was lower than the percent inhibition (~ 70%) at the elevated plasma glucose concentration of 13.9 mmol/L (250 mg/dL) in both populations.
